oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: The Craighead-Jackson House, located in Knoxville, Tennessee. The historical marker reads, "Craighead-Jackson House, 1818, Toms Memorial Collection."
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: The home, adjacent to the Blount Mansion, was the residence of John Craighead, a prominent businessman. Dr. George Jackson became the owner in the mid-nineteenth century until the late 1870s.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:source: RG 82: Tennessee Department of Conservation Photograph Collection, 1937-1976
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:subject: Houses; Architectural elements
